65. Demonstrate PHP script that checks if a string contains another string and displays the result.
ANSWER
<?php
// Main string
$mainString = "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.";
// Substring to search for
$searchString = "fox";
// Check if the substring exists in the main string
if (strpos($mainString, $searchString) !== false) {
    echo "✅ The string contains '$searchString'.";
} else {
    echo "❌ The string does NOT contain '$searchString'.";
}
?>

OUTPUT
The string contains 'fox'.
